3 (d) (1) The Ethics Commission shall provide a training course [of at least 2
4 hours] THROUGH ONLINE TRAINING OR LIVE PRESENTATION on the CONFLICT OF
5 INTEREST, FINANCIAL DISCLOSURE, RELEVANT ADMINISTRATIVE, AND OTHER
6 APPLICABLE requirements of the Maryland Public Ethics Law for an individual who:
7 (i) fills a vacancy in a position that has been identified as a public
8 official position under § 5–103 of this title;
9 (ii) serves in a position identified as a public official position under §
10 5–103 of this title; or
11 (iii) on or after January 19, 2023, is a State official that is subject to
12 the jurisdiction of the Ethics Commission under § 5–104(a) of this title.
13 (2) The individual shall complete the training course within 6 months of:
14 (i) filling a vacancy; or
15 (ii) a position being identified as a public official position.
16 (3) The training requirement under this subsection does not apply to an
17 individual who:
18 (i) except for a member of a board of license commissioners or a
19 liquor control board, is a public official only as a member of a commission, task force, or
20 similar entity; or
21 (ii) has completed a training course provided by the Ethics
22 Commission while serving in another public official position.
23 (e) (1) (i) The Ethics Commission shall provide a training course for
24 regulated lobbyists and prospective regulated lobbyists at least twice each year THROUGH
25 ONLINE TRAINING OR LIVE PRESENTATION on the provisions of the Maryland Public
26 Ethics Law, including provisions related to discrimination and harassment, relevant to
27 regulated lobbyists.
28 (ii) One training course shall be held each January.
29 (2) When a person initially registers as a regulated lobbyist, the Ethics
30 Commission shall provide the person with information on the provisions of the Maryland
31 Public Ethics Law relevant to regulated lobbyists.

